{"job_title": "Director of HR Tech", "job_location": "Jakarta - Indonesia", "job_department": "Logistics & Operations", "job_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs/e0d49257-69e8-4a1a-81bf-b8b0e91c7f4c", "first_seen": "2026-04-21 16:03:37", "base_salary": "0", "job_type": "Full-time", "job_level": "3 - 15 years", "job_apply_end_date": "2026-05-11 14:45:37", "last_seen": "2026-04-11 14:45:37", "is_active": "True", "company": "Sagara Technology Group", "company_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/companies/sagara-technology-group", "job_board": "Tech in Asia Jobs", "job_board_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs", "job_age": "recent", "work_arrangement": "On-site", "desc": "Director of HR Tech Logistics & Operations <p>This role exists to make Sagara <strong>win on trust through execution</strong>.<br>\n Not by saying we’re the best—but by building the systems that make clients <em>feel</em> we are the safest, clearest, most disciplined outsourcing partner in Indonesia.</p>\n<p>Your job is to ensure:</p>\n<ul><li>weak talent doesn’t enter the system (ASSESS), </li>\n  <li>placement is correct and delivery is visible (PLACE), </li>\n  <li>strong engineers become even stronger over time (IMPROVE).</li>\n</ul><p>Key Responsibilities\n</p>\n\n<ul><li>Design and run Sagara’s <strong>Ops Operating System</strong> for outsourcing at scale (Assess → Place → Improve) </li>\n  <li>Set “quality gates” so weak talent cannot slip into client delivery </li>\n  <li>Standardize client experience:  \n    <ul><li>onboarding checklist </li>\n      <li>reporting cadence </li>\n      <li>delivery visibility </li>\n      <li>replacement/continuity handling </li>\n    </ul></li>\n  <li>Build scorecards and dashboards for:  \n    <ul><li>talent quality </li>\n      <li>account health </li>\n      <li>engineering performance and improvement </li>\n    </ul></li>\n  <li>Align Sales promises with Delivery reality (no overcommitment) </li>\n  <li>Turn delivery discipline into market proof (so trust compounds)</li>\n</ul><p>What “Great” Looks Like\n</p>\n\n<p>A great Director in this role will:</p>\n<ul><li>make Sagara<strong> organized, modern, and calm</strong> to clients </li>\n  <li>reduce churn by improving placement accuracy and delivery visibility </li>\n  <li>raise the average engineer quality entering the system </li>\n  <li>increase delivery speed <em>while keeping coding quality stable</em> </li>\n  <li>create a repeatable machine that can scale to 100 active clients without chaos</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Talent / Assess</strong></p>\n<ul><li>pass-rate quality (higher bar, not higher volume) </li>\n  <li>time-to-fill for priority roles </li>\n  <li>“weak talent leakage” rate (should trend to near-zero) </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Placement / Client</strong></p>\n<ul><li>time-to-start (days from sign → kickoff) </li>\n  <li>client satisfaction / NPS </li>\n  <li>churn rate and escalation rate </li>\n  <li>weekly reporting compliance rate </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Engineering / Improve</strong></p>\n<ul><li>defect rate / rollback rate </li>\n  <li>cycle time (task start → shipped) </li>\n  <li>productivity uplift from tools + standards </li>\n  <li>engineering bench readiness score</li>\n</ul><p>Team Structure (Direct Reports)\n</p>\n\n<ul><li><strong>Tech Recruiter</strong> (Assessment &amp; recruitment engine) </li>\n  <li><strong>Tech Account Manager</strong> (Placement &amp; delivery visibility) </li>\n  <li><strong>Tech Engineering Manager</strong> (Continuous improvement &amp; quality discipline)  </li>\n</ul><p>Requirements\n</p>\n\n<ul><li>Strong experience in tech services/outsourcing operations, delivery, or engineering management </li>\n  <li>Systems thinker: you build repeatable processes, not heroic improvisation </li>\n  <li>Strong judgment on people quality, placement fit, and delivery risk </li>\n  <li>Comfortable with delivery tooling discipline (Jira, documentation rhythms, quality standards) </li>\n  <li>Clear written communication and executive-level updates </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The bottleneck is not talent supply alone.<br>\nThe bottleneck is <strong>trust at scale</strong>, and trust is built by:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>consistent quality filtering</strong> </li>\n  <li><strong>correct placement</strong> </li>\n  <li><strong>visible delivery</strong> </li>\n  <li><strong>continuous improvement</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>"}
