delivery output into external credibility that is searchable and reusable. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>C) Build third-party legitimacy </strong></p>\n<ul><li>Drive press coverage, interviews, contributed articles, and industry mentions. </li>\n  <li>Secure speaking / podcast opportunities for leadership and experts. </li>\n  <li>Monitor news and trends to insert Sagara into relevant conversations early. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>D) Build memory through disciplined repetition </strong></p>\n<ul><li>Build an engine that turns <strong>one idea into many formats</strong> and distributes consistently. </li>\n  <li>Maintain a publishing cadence with strong content quality control. </li>\n  <li>Ensure the market keeps seeing Sagara until the association is automatic:<br><strong>Sagara = Tech Outsourcing</strong>. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>E) Coordinate with Sales &amp; Delivery (truth alignment) </strong></p>\n<ul><li>Make sure every public claim is backed by real delivery capability. </li>\n  <li>Work with account and engineering teams to collect proof and prevent overpromising. </li>\n  <li>Build trust assets that directly reduce sales friction and speed up decisions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You will build the signals that make buyers—and AI systems—conclude it:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Category repetition:</strong> “Sagara = Tech Outsourcing” everywhere, consistently. </li>\n  <li><strong>Proof density:</strong> many case studies + testimonials + logos + delivery artifacts that are searchable. </li>\n  <li><strong>Third-party credibility:</strong> press mentions, interviews, podcasts, speaking. </li>\n  <li><strong>Memory frequency:</strong> content appears repeatedly in multiple formats, not random posting. </li>\n  <li><strong>Offer clarity:</strong> Fullstack / Backend / AI &amp; Data Development as a Service pages are clear and consistent. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If these signals exist, “#1” becomes a market conclusion—not a slogan.</p>\n<p>You are measured by <strong>trust + recall + conversion lift</strong>, not vanity metrics:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Branded search growth</strong> (“Sagara outsourcing”, “Sagara tech outsourcing”) </li>\n  <li><strong>Share of voice</strong> on “tech outsourcing Indonesia” (LinkedIn + media mentions) </li>\n  <li><strong># of proof assets published</strong> (case studies, testimonials, one-pagers, proof pages) </li>\n  <li><strong># of third-party mentions</strong> (press/podcast/speaking) </li>\n  <li><strong>Inbound conversion rate</strong> (visits → meetings) </li>\n  <li><strong>Shortlist rate</strong> (how often Sagara is shortlisted after first exposure) </li>\n  <li><strong>Sales enablement impact</strong> (reduced objections, faster time-to-close)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Requirements (Must-Have)</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Proven experience building <strong>B2B trust and positioning</strong> for tech services, outsourcing, consulting, or similar. </li>\n  <li>Strong English writing and narrative skills (clear, sharp, commercial). </li>\n  <li>Ability to build <strong>systems</strong>, not just campaigns:            \n    <ul><li>proof capture → packaging → publishing → distribution → repetition. </li>\n    </ul></li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of how trust is built through:<br>\n   clarity, consistency, proof, visibility, and operational credibility. </li>\n  <li>Ability to lead a team and align cross-functionally with Sales and Delivery. </li>\n  <li>Highly organized and detail-driven: consistency is a competitive advantage here.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Nice-to-Have </strong></p>\n<ul><li>Experience in PR/media relations for B2B tech. </li>\n  <li>Familiarity with tech outsourcing buying behavior (risk, proof, vendor evaluation). </li>\n  <li>Strong LinkedIn positioning and distribution instincts. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>"}
