 to buy, retain, and expand with Sagara.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with marketing and sales teams to align ads, targeting, landing pages, messaging, and follow-up.</li>\n  <li>Improve performance across click quality, lead quality, meeting conversion, and pipeline contribution.</li>\n  <li>Ensure Sagara appears consistently in front of the right market with a strong, serious, and trusted presence.</li>\n  <li>Use performance data to improve budget allocation, channel focus, and growth decisions over time.</li>\n  <li>Graduated from Informatics or Computer Science.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>\n</p>\n\n<ul><li>Strong understanding of B2B demand generation, paid growth, retargeting, and pipeline-building.</li>\n  <li>Must be highly proficient in <strong>LinkedIn Ads</strong> and willing to become deeply expert in using it as Sagara’s primary paid channel for reaching the right decision makers and building serious market presence.</li>\n  <li>Strong familiarity with Google Search Ads and digital campaign performance optimization.</li>\n  <li>Understanding of how ads, audience targeting, landing pages, and follow-up systems work together to generate qualified pipeline.</li>\n  <li>Able to use performance data to identify winning channels, remove weak campaigns, and scale what works.</li>\n  <li>Proven experience in growth marketing, paid media, performance marketing, pipeline generation, or similar roles. Fresh graduates with strong internship or project experience are welcome.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication and collaboration skills across marketing, sales, and leadership teams.</li>\n  <li>Detail-oriented, highly organized, and able to manage multiple campaigns and experiments at once.</li>\n  <li>Willing to work full on-site in Jakarta.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>"}
