{"job_title": "AI & Data Engineer (AI-Native Technologist)", "job_location": "Jakarta - Indonesia", "job_department": "Software Engineer", "job_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs/e8e1f328-4dea-480c-8cfe-7a5ab01f8f13", "first_seen": "2026-04-21 16:03:37", "base_salary": "5500000", "job_type": "Full-time", "job_level": "3 - 15 years", "job_apply_end_date": "2026-05-11 12:44:52", "last_seen": "2026-04-11 12:44:52", "is_active": "True", "company": "Sagara Technology Group", "company_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/companies/sagara-technology-group", "job_board": "Tech in Asia Jobs", "job_board_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs", "job_age": "recent", "work_arrangement": "On-site", "desc": "AI & Data Engineer (AI-Native Technologist) Software Engineer <p><strong>Sagara Technology: A Tech Outsourcing Company</strong></p>\n<p>Sagara Technology is Indonesia’s AI-native tech outsourcing partner. We build production systems that help governments, enterprises, and fast-growing companies ship faster—with measurable delivery, strong engineering discipline, and modern workflows.</p>\n<p>As an AI &amp; Data Engineer, you won’t be doing “research for research.” You will build real AI and data systems that run in production: pipelines, retrieval, analytics, automation, and AI-powered features that drive outcomes.</p>\n<p><strong>We’re hiring urgently for fast fulfillment. If you can ship, we move fast.<br><br>\nWhat You’ll Do</strong></p>\n<p>You will design, build, and operate AI/data systems end-to-end—from ingestion to production deployment.</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Build and maintain <strong>data pipelines</strong> (batch + streaming when needed) with strong observability. </li>\n  <li>Design <strong>data models</strong> and optimize queries in <strong>Postgres/Supabase</strong> for analytics and product features. </li>\n  <li>Build AI-enabled features such as:  <strong>RAG / retrieval pipelines</strong>, embeddings, indexing, and relevance evaluation, <strong>LLM-powered automation</strong> (classification, summarization, extraction, routing) &amp; <strong>analytics &amp; reporting layers</strong> for product decision-making </li>\n  <li>Create reliable <strong>APIs/services</strong> in Python for AI and data workloads. </li>\n  <li>Implement <strong>caching</strong> strategies using <strong>Redis</strong> for speed and cost control. </li>\n  <li>Write <strong>tests</strong>, monitor quality, and harden systems for production reliability. </li>\n  <li>Ship through <strong>CI/CD</strong> using GitHub Actions and containerized delivery with Docker. </li>\n  <li>Communicate clearly: tradeoffs, risks, costs, and progress updates.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong><br>\nOur Engineering Stack (Daily Use)</strong></p>\n<p>We’re an AI-native engineering team. You’ll use:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Cursor + Claude Code + Aider + MCP</strong> for AI-assisted development and refactoring </li>\n  <li><strong>Python</strong> for data/AI services and pipelines </li>\n  <li><strong>Docker</strong> for reproducible environments and deployment </li>\n  <li><strong>GitHub Actions</strong> for CI/CD, checks, and automation </li>\n  <li><strong>Supabase/Postgres</strong> for data, auth, storage (as needed) </li>\n  <li><strong>Redis</strong> for caching, queues, rate-limiting, and fast state </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We don’t hire people who “try AI tools.” We hire engineers who can use them responsibly to <strong>ship faster without sacrificing correctness</strong>.</p>\n<p><br><strong>What “Great” Looks Like at Sagara</strong></p>\n<p><strong>A strong AI &amp; Data Engineer at Sagara:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Can take ambiguous requirements and produce a reliable system design. </li>\n  <li>Thinks in <strong>latency, cost, and reliability</strong>, not just model quality. </li>\n  <li>Understands data correctness and can debug “silent failures.” </li>\n  <li>Knows that production AI needs:  \n    <ul><li>evaluation, </li>\n      <li>guardrails, </li>\n      <li>monitoring, </li>\n      <li>and iteration loops. </li>\n    </ul></li>\n  <li>Writes clean documentation and communicates like a professional.<br></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Requirements (Must-Have)</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Strong fundamentals in <strong>Python</strong> and system debugging. </li>\n  <li>Comfortable working with <strong>Postgres</strong> (schema design, SQL, performance). </li>\n  <li>Experience building at least one of the following:  \n    <ul><li>data pipelines, </li>\n      <li>analytics/reporting systems, </li>\n      <li>production AI features (LLM/RAG/classification/extraction), </li>\n      <li>caching/queue patterns using Redis. </li>\n    </ul></li>\n  <li>Can containerize work in <strong>Docker</strong> and ship via CI/CD. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong><br>\nEducation</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Final-year students or fresh graduates in CS/IS/Engineering are welcome <strong>if your portfolio proves you can ship</strong>. </li>\n  <li>Non-degree candidates are welcome with strong evidence (GitHub + deployed systems + case writeups).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Why Join Sagara</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Build <strong>real production AI systems</strong>, not demos. </li>\n  <li>Learn AI-native workflows used by top global teams. </li>\n  <li>Work with disciplined delivery: weekly demos, measurable output, strong standards. </li>\n  <li>Accelerate your career through high-bar engineering culture.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>"}
