 <li>Collaborate tightly with engineers, QA, and product stakeholders. </li>\n  <li>Participate in code reviews and ship through CI/CD with clean release practices. </li>\n  <li>Communicate clearly: progress, blockers, tradeoffs, and decisions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Our Delivery Stack (You’ll Use This Daily)</strong></p>\n<p>We’re an AI-native engineering team. You’ll use:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>v0</strong> for rapid UI scaffolding and iteration </li>\n  <li><strong>Cursor + Claude Code + Continue + MCP</strong> for AI-assisted development and refactoring </li>\n  <li><strong>TypeScript + Node.js</strong> </li>\n  <li><strong>Supabase</strong> (DB/Auth/Storage) when suitable </li>\n  <li><strong>Vercel</strong> for deployment and environments </li>\n  <li><strong>GitHub Actions</strong> for CI/CD, checks, and automation </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We don’t hire people who “fear tools.” We hire people who can use tools responsibly to <strong>ship faster without sacrificing clarity or quality</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>What “Great” Looks Like at Sagara</strong></p>\n<p>We care about outcomes, not vibes. A strong Full-Stack Engineer at Sagara:</p>\n<ul><li>Can debug issues quickly and explain root causes clearly. </li>\n  <li>Understands tradeoffs (speed vs quality, short-term vs long-term). </li>\n  <li>Writes code that other engineers can maintain. </li>\n  <li>Can move fast under a weekly delivery cadence. </li>\n  <li>Communicates like a professional—especially in written updates. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Requirements (Must-Have)</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Working knowledge of <strong>JavaScript/TypeScript</strong>. </li>\n  <li>Comfortable building web apps end-to-end (frontend + backend).</li>\n  <li>Experience with at least one modern framework: <strong>React / Vue</strong> (React preferred). </li>\n  <li>Basic backend understanding: APIs, databases, auth, and deployment basics. </li>\n  <li>Strong ownership, discipline, and ability to work in a team. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Education</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Informatics/Information Systems are welcome. </li>\n  <li>High-school graduates from Software Engineering programs are welcome <strong>if your portfolio proves you can ship</strong>. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>"}
{"job_title": "Tech Engineering Manager", "job_location": "Jakarta - Indonesia", "job_department": "Software Engineer", "job_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs/2c1618c1-626d-4b05-bce9-c0bda6bf6e24", "first_seen": "2026-04-21 16:03:37", "base_salary": "6000000", "job_type": "Full-time", "job_level": "2 - 15 years", "job_apply_end_date": "2026-05-11 12:11:43", "last_seen": "2026-04-11 12:11:43", "is_active": "True", "company": "Sagara Technology Group", "company_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/companies/sagara-technology-group", "job_board": "Tech in Asia Jobs", "job_board_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs", "job_age": "recent", "work_arrangement": "On-site", "desc": "Tech Engineering Manager Software Engineer <p><strong>Expected Outcome</strong></p>\n<p>Build Sagara’s engineering improvement system into a structured, repeatable, and high-performance engine that continuously increases developer productivity, coding quality, technology adaptability, and delivery speed.</p>\n<p>This role is expected to help position Sagara as a trusted tech outsourcing vendor from Indonesia with a disciplined engineering engine behind it—one that keeps getting sharper, faster, and more relevant over time.</p>\n<p><strong>Role Purpose</strong></p>\n<p>The Tech Engineering Manager is responsible for making strong tech resources even stronger.</p>\n<p>This role does not exist to manage engineers passively. It exists to build a continuous improvement system that raises output quality, strengthens engineering discipline, and ensures Sagara’s developers stay productive, adaptable, and delivery-ready.</p>\n<p>The goal is engineering excellence, stronger delivery, and continuous upgrading.</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Build and improve Sagara’s engineering excellence system to continuously raise the quality and performance of its developer bench.</li>\n  <li>Use Cursor as a core engineering productivity tool to improve coding speed, technical clarity, and day-to-day execution quality.</li>\n  <li>Apply Claude Pro and Continue Code as supporting tools to strengthen engineering workflows, code assistance, review discipline, and continuous learning.</li>\n  <li>Build an engineering culture that increases productivity, coding quality stability, adaptability to new technologies, and delivery speed.</li>\n  <li>Create and maintain structured standards for engineering work, including coding discipline, documentation habits, workflow consistency, and technical review quality.</li>\n  <li>Ensure developers are continuously improving not only in code, but also in communication, clarity of thinking, and delivery maturity.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Build an internal culture where:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>everyone writes</li>\n  <li>everyone presents</li>\n  <li>everyone is tested under pressure</li>\n  <li>Work closely with recruiter, account, and leadership teams to ensure engineering growth is aligned with client expectations and real delivery needs.</li>\n  <li>Identify engineering gaps, skill weaknesses, workflow inefficiencies, and areas where AI tools can improve output and consistency.</li>\n  <li>Build repeatable systems for coaching, technical development, performance improvement, and engineering readiness across Sagara’s core delivery roles.</li>\n  <li>Continuously improve how engineering quality is measured, reviewed, and strengthened over time.</li>\n  <li>Help make Sagara’s engineering team more relevant, sharper, and harder to compete with in the market.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Strong ability to lead and improve software engineering teams, workflows, or delivery quality in technology services, software development, or outsourcing environments.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of how to improve engineering productivity, code quality, and delivery performance in a structured and repeatable way.</li>\n  <li>Must be highly proficient in Cursor and willing to become deeply expert in using it as Sagara’s primary engineering productivity tool.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with Claude Pro, Continue Code, and AI-assisted coding workflows is a strong advantage.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of coding quality, technical review standards, engineering workflows, and continuous improvement systems.</li>\n  <li>Strong ability to coach engineers in both technical execution and communication discipline.</li>\n  <li>Proven experience in engineering management, technical leadership, software delivery, or similar roles. Fresh graduates with strong internship or project leadership experience are welcome.</li>\n  <li>Strong judgment in evaluating engineering quality, performance, readiness, and long-term growth potential.</li>\n  <li>Strong analytical skills in identifying bottlenecks, weak points, and opportunities to improve engineering output.</li>\n  <li>Strong collaboration skills across engineering, recruiter, account, and leadership teams.</li>\n  <li>Detail-oriented, highly organized, and able to manage multiple developers, workflows, and quality standards at once.</li>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, Information Systems, or a related field.</li>\n  <li>Willing to work full on-site in Jakarta.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong><br>\nWhat Great Looks Like in This Role</strong></p>\n<p><strong>A strong Tech Engineering Manager at Sagara will:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Make developers more productive without lowering quality</li>\n  <li>Make coding quality more stable and repeatable</li>\n  <li>Help engineers adapt faster to new tools and technologies</li>\n  <li>Increase delivery speed while keeping execution disciplined</li>\n  <li>Build a stronger engineering culture through writing, presentation, and pressure-tested growth</li>\n  <li>Help position Sagara as a trusted tech outsourcing vendor from Indonesia with a real engine of continuous engineering improvement </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>"}
