 highly proficient in Jira and willing to become deeply expert in using it as Sagara’s primary delivery visibility and coordination platform.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with Notion for account notes, project summaries, documentation, and client-facing clarity.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of how clients evaluate outsourcing vendors through speed, clarity, organization, reporting, and consistency.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication skills in English, especially in client-facing coordination and structured updates.</li>\n  <li>Strong ability to manage multiple accounts, moving parts, and delivery expectations at once.</li>\n  <li>Proven experience in account management, client service, delivery coordination, project coordination, or similar roles. Fresh graduates with strong internship or project experience are welcome.</li>\n  <li>Strong judgment in managing priorities, identifying issues early, and maintaining calm, professional communication.</li>\n  <li>Strong collaboration skills across recruiter, engineering, sales, and leadership teams.</li>\n  <li>Detail-oriented, highly organized, and able to keep account data, progress, and communication structured and reusable.</li>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Information Technology, Engineering, Human Resources, Finance or a related field.</li>\n  <li>Willing to work full on-site in Jakarta.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>What Great Looks Like in This Role</strong></p>\n<p><strong>A strong Tech Account Manager at Sagara will:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>place the right talent into the right client situation</li>\n  <li>make progress easier for clients to see and trust</li>\n  <li>make Sagara feel more professional, neat, modern, and calm</li>\n  <li>reduce confusion between client expectation and delivery execution</li>\n  <li>help position Sagara as a trusted tech outsourcing vendor from Indonesia with stronger delivery clarity and account control.</li>\n</ul>"}
