dentify strong technical talent and uncover high-potential candidates.</li>\n  <li>Apply <strong>TestGorilla</strong>, <strong>Sagara Certif</strong>, hackathons, and related filters to assess business mindset, communication potential, discipline, and practical readiness.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate and strengthen Sagara’s internal panel process for final evaluation of communication quality, character, and cultural fit.</li>\n  <li>Build a recruitment process that tests not only technical ability, but also business awareness, clarity, integrity, patience, and execution readiness.</li>\n  <li>Continuously improve how candidates are screened, scored, and categorized across technical quality, communication quality, and delivery suitability.</li>\n  <li>Build and maintain a strong pipeline of candidates across Sagara’s core delivery roles and target talent profiles.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with account, engineering, and leadership teams to align hiring standards with real client needs and delivery expectations.</li>\n  <li>Ensure recruitment data, scores, talent notes, and assessment outcomes are organized and reusable.</li>\n  <li>Continuously improve Sagara’s reputation as a serious place for top engineering talent by keeping the bar high and the process credible.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br><br><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Strong ability to recruit and assess technical talent for software development, engineering, or related digital roles.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of how to evaluate talent beyond CVs—especially through technical tests, structured assessments, and quality filters.</li>\n  <li>Must be highly proficient in <strong>HackerRank</strong> and willing to become deeply expert in using it as Sagara’s primary technical assessment platform.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with hackathons, technical hiring platforms, online coding tests, and structured screening systems.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of how to assess both technical capability and practical delivery readiness.</li>\n  <li>Strong judgment in evaluating communication, business awareness, discipline, and character—not just coding skill.</li>\n  <li>Proven experience in tech recruitment, talent assessment, hiring operations, or similar roles. Fresh graduates with strong internship or project experience are welcome.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with tools such as TestGorilla, assessment platforms, talent sourcing platforms, and recruitment workflows is a strong advantage.</li>\n  <li>Strong analytical skills in reviewing candidate performance, assessment outcomes, and talent quality signals.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication and coordination skills across recruiter, engineering, account, and leadership teams.</li>\n  <li>Detail-oriented, highly organized, and able to manage multiple hiring pipelines and candidate evaluations at once.</li>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Human Resources, Psychology, Business, Information Technology, Engineering, or a related field.</li>\n  <li>Willing to work full on-site in Jakarta.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>What Great Looks Like in This Role<br><br>\nA strong Tech Recruiter at Sagara will:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>keep weak talent out of the system</li>\n  <li>raise the average quality of candidates entering Sagara</li>\n  <li>make technical filtering more objective, more credible, and more repeatable</li>\n  <li>identify candidates who are not only technically strong, but also more ready for real delivery</li>\n  <li>help position Sagara as a trusted home for top technology developers in Indonesia </li>\n  <li>Sagara is building toward a stronger position: a trusted tech outsourcing vendor from Indonesia with a disciplined talent engine behind it.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>"}
