{"job_title": "Software Developer (Student Trainee)", "job_location": "Jakarta - Indonesia", "job_department": "Web Development", "job_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs/e9195428-9855-47e8-937b-ba34a53a8396", "first_seen": "2026-04-21 16:03:37", "base_salary": "0", "job_type": "Freelance", "job_level": "1 - 4 years", "job_apply_end_date": "2026-05-10 07:24:18", "last_seen": "2026-04-10 07:24:18", "is_active": "True", "company": "Sagara Technology Group", "company_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/companies/sagara-technology-group", "job_board": "Tech in Asia Jobs", "job_board_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs", "job_age": "recent", "work_arrangement": "On-site", "desc": "Software Developer (Student Trainee) Web Development <p><strong>Software Developer (Student Trainee)<br><br>\nSagara Technology: A Tech Outsourcing Company</strong></p>\n<p>Sagara Technology builds production software that solves real problems—fast, clean, and measurable. We partner with leading government institutions, enterprises, and fast-growing companies to deliver digital systems that improve performance at scale.</p>\n<p>Joining Sagara means you don’t just “work on tickets.” You join a team that ships real products and runs world-class delivery: clear SLAs, weekly demos, high quality standards, and modern AI-native engineering workflows.</p>\n<p><strong>We’re hiring for fast fulfillment. If you can ship, we’ll move quickly.</strong><br></p>\n<p><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p>\n<p>You will build and ship production software end-to-end—frontend to backend—inside a structured delivery cadence.</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Build <strong>stable, testable, production-grade</strong> features (not prototypes). </li>\n  <li>Develop and maintain <strong>TypeScript/Node.js</strong> services and APIs. </li>\n  <li>Build modern frontends and product flows (web apps, dashboards, internal tools). </li>\n  <li>Write automated tests, improve reliability, and prevent regressions. </li>\n  <li>Collaborate tightly with engineers, QA, and product stakeholders. </li>\n  <li>Participate in code reviews and ship through CI/CD with clean release practices. </li>\n  <li>Communicate clearly: progress, blockers, tradeoffs, and decisions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Our Delivery Stack (You’ll Use This Daily)</strong></p>\n<p>We’re an AI-native engineering team. You’ll use:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>v0</strong> for rapid UI scaffolding and iteration </li>\n  <li><strong>Cursor + Claude Code + Continue + MCP</strong> for AI-assisted development and refactoring </li>\n  <li><strong>TypeScript + Node.js</strong> </li>\n  <li><strong>Supabase</strong> (DB/Auth/Storage) when suitable </li>\n  <li><strong>Vercel</strong> for deployment and environments </li>\n  <li><strong>GitHub Actions</strong> for CI/CD, checks, and automation </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We don’t hire people who “fear tools.” We hire people who can use tools responsibly to <strong>ship faster without sacrificing clarity or quality</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>What “Great” Looks Like at Sagara</strong></p>\n<p>We care about outcomes, not vibes. A strong Full-Stack Engineer at Sagara:</p>\n<ul><li>Can debug issues quickly and explain root causes clearly. </li>\n  <li>Understands tradeoffs (speed vs quality, short-term vs long-term). </li>\n  <li>Writes code that other engineers can maintain. </li>\n  <li>Can move fast under a weekly delivery cadence. </li>\n  <li>Communicates like a professional—especially in written updates. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Requirements (Must-Have)</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Working knowledge of <strong>JavaScript/TypeScript</strong>. </li>\n  <li>Comfortable building web apps end-to-end (frontend + backend).</li>\n  <li>Experience with at least one modern framework: <strong>React / Vue</strong> (React preferred). </li>\n  <li>Basic backend understanding: APIs, databases, auth, and deployment basics. </li>\n  <li>Strong ownership, discipline, and ability to work in a team. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Education</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Informatics/Information Systems are welcome. </li>\n  <li>High-school graduates from Software Engineering programs are welcome <strong>if your portfolio proves you can ship</strong>. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>"}
