{"job_title": "Technical Product Analyst", "job_location": "Jakarta - Indonesia", "job_department": "Software Engineer", "job_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs/fcca6c62-7b47-4bb7-96f2-c509c64d74e4", "first_seen": "2026-04-21 16:03:37", "base_salary": "6000000", "job_type": "Full-time", "job_level": "0 - 2 years", "job_apply_end_date": "2026-05-06 02:41:25", "last_seen": "2026-04-06 02:41:25", "is_active": "True", "company": "Deliveree On-Demand Logistics (Southeast Asia)", "company_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/companies/deliveree-on-demand-logistics-southeast-asia", "job_board": "Tech in Asia Jobs", "job_board_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs", "job_age": "recent", "work_arrangement": "On-site", "desc": "Technical Product Analyst Software Engineer <p><em>If you just click apply, you will not receive a response. You must follow the instructions below under 'how to apply' for our team to review and respond to your application. Complete and qualified applications receive a response within 24 hours.</em></p>\n<p><strong>SUMMARY OF OPPORTUNITY</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Company: Deliveree, a pre-IPO logistics technology company</li>\n  <li>Title: Technical Product Analyst</li>\n  <li>Reporting: Principle Product Manager</li>\n  <li>Locations: Jakarta, Indonesia</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>PURPOSE OF THE ROLE</strong></p>\n<p>Deliveree is a fast moving, rapidly growing, and very successful logistics technology company that is changing the cargo and trucking industry in Indonesia, Thailand and Philippines to reduce waste, grow the economy, create jobs, and make the logistics industry more competitive.</p>\n<p>For our Technical Product Analyst position, we are seeking talented, ambitious, hard working, and career-minded candidates with a degree in computer science, Information communication technology, information systems, or related from a recognized university. Having some experience as a Technical Product Analyst with strong English communications skills is preferred. </p>\n<p>You should have a keen interest in business and be willing to prioritize an accelerated career as your highest priority. We believe that anything is possible if you want it badly enough. </p>\n<p>When you interview with us, you will be considered for an assignment in Jakarta, Indonesia in-country product team who closely work with the country directors, group executives, and other markets product teams. </p>\n<p>If this description excites you, please read our qualification requirements below.</p>\n<p><strong>WHAT WILL YOU DO</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Work with stakeholders to identify opportunities and process improvements by leveraging organization data to drive business solutions.</li>\n  <li>Conduct analysis to understand the bugs or requests from stakeholders.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with Product Team, Design and Engineering to specify requirements, and ensure features are being implemented according to business expectations.</li>\n  <li>Gather market trends and internal data to conduct business analysis and provide recommendations and enhancements to the business.</li>\n  <li>Assist with product localization to include but not limited to: translation, usability, local documentation, configurations and settings.</li>\n  <li>Participate in user acceptance testing and create documentation and user manuals for business.</li>\n  <li>Provide progressive status and updates to stakeholders, product and project management.</li>\n  <li>Any other tasks assigned by the company from time to time.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>QUALIFICATIONS</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Fresh graduates or up to 2 years experience are welcome to apply.</li>\n  <li>Required undergraduate degree from Engineering major.</li>\n  <li>Good verbal and written English communication skills with good presentation skills.</li>\n  <li>Good skills in problem solving, analyzing data, requirement gathering and documentation with attention to detail.</li>\n  <li>A user-centric mindset with UI/UX experience and skills in using tools for business modeling, technical diagrams, and business diagrams.</li>\n  <li>Good skills in critical thinking, stakeholder management, and communication skills.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>BENEFITS</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Competitive monthly salary</li>\n  <li>Merit-based promotions</li>\n  <li>Full private healthcare coverage</li>\n  <li>Annual paid leave</li>\n  <li>13th-month bonus</li>\n  <li>Remote working for 6 weeks every year. Available during Ramadan and Christmas</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>HOW TO APPLY</strong></p>\n<p>Submit the below items via email to christine@deliveree.com - If you submit all the required materials and your qualifications fit our search, you will hear back from us within 24 hours.</p>\n<ol><li>Brief cover email</li>\n  <li>PDF resume</li>\n  <li>Completed pre-interview form</li>\n  <li>University grade or transcript</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Download Pre-Interview Form: https://dlvr.ee/2CzPe0I </p>\n<p><strong>DELIVEREE LINKS</strong></p>\n<ul><li>https://www.deliveree.com/logistics-investment-summary/ </li>\n  <li>https://www.linkedin.com/company/deliveree-on-demand-logistics-southeast-asia/ </li>\n  <li>https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/deliveree</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>DELIVEREE OFFICE TOUR</strong></p>\n<ul><li>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=giz5WrjkRO0 </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>"}
