{"job_title": "Secretary of Commissioner", "job_location": "Jakarta - Indonesia", "job_department": "Executive & Management", "job_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs/57750dbd-cb5b-412c-a426-72a5f8250298", "first_seen": "2026-04-21 16:03:37", "base_salary": "6000000", "job_type": "Contract", "job_level": "3 - 5 years", "job_apply_end_date": "2026-04-12 07:59:29", "last_seen": "2026-03-13 07:59:29", "is_active": "True", "company": "TLab", "company_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/companies/tlab", "job_board": "Tech in Asia Jobs", "job_board_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs", "job_age": "expired", "work_arrangement": "On-site", "desc": "Secretary of Commissioner Executive & Management <p><strong>Responsibilities : </strong></p>\n<p>1. Prepare and organize the work agenda and activities of the Commissioners.</p>\n<p>2. Schedule internal and external meetings, including those with the Board of Directors, shareholders, business partners, and regulators.</p>\n<p>3. Arrange travel arrangements and logistical needs for the Commissioners.</p>\n<p>4. Create, store, and manage archives and important documents related to the Commissioners' activities.</p>\n<p>5. Prepare minutes of Commissioners' meetings, General Meetings of Shareholders (GMS), and meetings with the Board of Directors.</p>\n<p>6. Prepare reports on the Commissioners' routine activities and prepare supporting documents for decisions.</p>\n<p>7. Serve as a liaison between the Commissioners and the Board of Directors, management, shareholders, and external parties.</p>\n<p>8. Convey information, decisions, and directions to the Commissioners in a timely, clear, and confidential manner.</p>\n<p>9. Foster professional working relationships with business partners, the government, and regulators.</p>\n<p>10. Assist the Commissioners in ensuring compliance with company regulations, laws, and Good Corporate Governance (GCG).</p>\n<p>11. Support the preparation of presentation materials, annual reports, and official documents required for the supervisory function.</p>\n<p>12. Ensure the confidentiality of all documents, communications, and strategic company data.</p>\n<p>13. Manage access to information related to the Commissioners in a professional manner and in accordance with company security standards.</p>\n<p>14. Coordinate with the Corporate Secretary, Legal, and Management departments to ensure the smooth administration of the Commissioners' work.</p>\n<p>15. Assist in the preparation of reports or documents required for audits, compliance, or regulatory purposes.</p>\n<p>16. Ensure that all Commissioners' work needs (administration, documents, communications) are available on time.</p>\n<p>17. Responsible for managing petty cash for the Commissioners' needs.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements : </strong></p>\n<p>1. Minimum Bachelor's degree in any major (preferably Business Administration/Management/Economy) with a GPA of 3.00.</p>\n<p>2. Minimum of 3 years of experience as a Secretary.</p>\n<p>3. Good communication skills.</p>\n<p>4. Good English skills.</p>\n<p>5. Proficient in MS Office and Google Workspace.</p>\n<p>6. Maintaining the company's image through a polite and professional demeanor and appearance.</p>\n<p>7. Able to work under pressure and with deadlines.</p>\n<p>8. High integrity and maintaining confidentiality of information.</p>\n<p>9. Agile, alert, and responsive, disciplined, and able to work independently and in a team.</p>\n<p>10. Knowledge of IT (Point Plus)</p>\n<p><br></p>"}
