{"job_title": "Brand Marketing Manager", "job_location": "Jakarta - Indonesia", "job_department": "Marketing & PR", "job_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs/3465d8f6-183b-4c4b-8741-b453e7d9cf3a", "first_seen": "2026-04-21 16:03:37", "base_salary": "12000000", "job_type": "Full-time", "job_level": "4 - 6 years", "job_apply_end_date": "2026-04-10 02:57:53", "last_seen": "2026-03-11 02:57:53", "is_active": "True", "company": "Little Joy Indonesia", "company_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/companies/little-joy-indonesia-1", "job_board": "Tech in Asia Jobs", "job_board_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs", "job_age": "expired", "work_arrangement": "On-site", "desc": "Brand Marketing Manager Marketing & PR <p><strong>Brand Marketing Manager</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Little Joy Indonesia</strong></p>\n<p>The Brand Marketing Manager is responsible for building, strengthening, and scaling the Little Joy brand as a trusted nutritional partner for mothers and children. This role leads end-to-end brand strategy from awareness to loyalty through a data-driven, consumer-centric, and business-oriented approach.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p>• Develop and execute the annual brand marketing strategy aligned with the company’s vision and growth targets.</p>\n<p>• Strengthen and maintain brand positioning, brand voice, and brand identity across all online and offline touchpoints.</p>\n<p>• Lead ads planning and strategic direction, ensuring paid campaigns align with brand objectives, target audiences, and funnel priorities in collaboration with the performance team.</p>\n<p>• Plan and execute brand campaigns (ATL, BTL, digital, community, KOL/influencer) to drive brand awareness, consideration, and trust.</p>\n<p>• Lead partnership execution, including co-branding initiatives, community collaborations, strategic partners, and brand activations that support brand growth and visibility.</p>\n<p>• Own and oversee CRM strategy, ensuring customer lifecycle communication (acquisition, engagement, retention, repurchase, loyalty) is aligned with brand values and business goals.</p>\n<p>• Collaborate closely with Digital Marketing, Creative, E-Commerce, Product, and CRM teams to ensure consistent, personalized, and relevant brand messaging across all customer touchpoints.</p>\n<p>• Manage and track brand and CRM performance metrics, including brand awareness, engagement, share of voice, customer retention, repurchase rate, and customer lifetime value.</p>\n<p>• Conduct market, consumer, and competitor analysis to identify insights, trends, and opportunities for brand and CRM optimization.</p>\n<p>• Manage brand marketing budgets effectively with a strong ROI and accountability mindset.</p>\n<p>• Oversee the development of branding assets, including key visuals, brand guidelines, campaign concepts, storytelling frameworks, and CRM communication guidelines.</p>\n<p>• Lead, mentor, and develop the brand and CRM-related team functions to build a high-performing and agile organization.</p>\n<p>• Ensure all branding, advertising, partnership, and CRM communications comply with regulatory standards, product claims, and ethical guidelines for mother-and-child products.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p><strong>• </strong>Minimum 4–6 years of experience in Brand Marketing, preferably within FMCG, nutrition, or consumer goods industries.</p>\n<p>• Proven experience in brand campaign leadership, ads planning, strategic partnerships, and CRM initiatives.</p>\n<p>• Strong strategic thinking with hands-on execution capability across branding, paid media, and customer lifecycle management.</p>\n<p>• Ability to collaborate cross-functionally and translate business objectives into effective brand, ads, partnership, and CRM strategies.</p>\n<p>• Solid understanding of mother-and-child consumer behavior, digital marketing ecosystem, and CRM best practices.</p>\n<p>• Data-driven mindset with the ability to interpret insights from ads performance, CRM metrics, and market research.</p>\n<p>• Strong leadership, communication, and stakeholder management skills.</p>\n<p>• Adaptive, growth-oriented, and comfortable working in a fast-paced startup environment.</p>\n<p><br></p>"}
