ows momentum, deal terms, partner negotiations, and basic budgets—so planning and execution stay sharp and future-facing.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>3+ years</strong> experience in <strong>account management / project management / operations / strategy</strong> (agency, partnerships, entertainment, media, events, or fast-moving startups). </li>\n  <li>Proven track record leading <strong>multiple projects</strong> at once with tight deadlines and many stakeholders. </li>\n  <li>Strong <strong>client/stakeholder handling</strong>: you can say no, negotiate scope, and keep relationships warm + professional.</li>\n  <li>Excellent <strong>planning &amp; execution</strong> skills: scopes, timelines, priorities, and delivery quality.</li>\n  <li>High <strong>taste + attention to detail</strong>—you care about how things land, not just that they’re done.</li>\n  <li>Clear, kind, direct communicator (written + verbal); comfortable running calls and writing updates.</li>\n  <li>Comfortable working in a culture-driven environment (nightlife rhythms happen sometimes), while keeping structure and calm.</li>\n  <li>Tools: Docs/Sheets, basic decks.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Nice to Have:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Experience in <strong>music/nightlife</strong>, talent management, label services, or live events.</li>\n  <li>Experience shaping and executing <strong>brand partnerships</strong> (deliverables, approvals, reporting).</li>\n  <li>Content workflow familiarity (shoot planning, asset lists, creative briefs, release calendars).</li>\n</ul>"}
{"job_title": "Solutions Engineer Intern", "job_location": "Jakarta - Indonesia", "job_department": "IT Engineer", "job_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs/6d5a7178-2d9a-4eb1-995d-d902e21e26ab", "first_seen": "2026-04-21 16:03:37", "base_salary": "0", "job_type": "Internship", "job_level": "0 - 15 years", "job_apply_end_date": "2026-04-05 10:50:04", "last_seen": "2026-03-06 10:50:04", "is_active": "True", "company": "Ematic Solutions", "company_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/companies/ematic-solutions", "job_board": "Tech in Asia Jobs", "job_board_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs", "job_age": "expired", "work_arrangement": "On-site", "desc": "Solutions Engineer Intern IT Engineer <p><strong>About Us</strong></p>\n<p>Ematic Solutions is pioneering Southeast Asia’s AI Agency model, moving beyond a traditional digital agency to a company engineered for the AI age. Our mission is to infuse AI into everything we do, helping organizations build and optimize high-ROI digital ecosystems. We are a profitable, scalable business with a deep technical DNA and an AI-native workforce. We’re looking for AI-savvy, forward-thinking individuals who are excited to shape the future of marketing with us.<br></p>\n<p><strong>What's The Gig?</strong></p>\n<p>In this role, you’ll be part of a lean, innovative, and profitable team that’s engineered for the future of marketing. You’ll work hands-on with AI-powered tools, scalable service models, and multi-market campaigns, delivering real impact for leading organizations. Expect a fast-paced environment where you’ll learn, experiment, and grow as we embed AI into everything we do — from strategy to execution.</p>\n<p><strong>Your Responsibilities Will Include:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Be part of challenging assignments and internal projects that contribute to business growth</li>\n  <li>Provide customer and technical support related to the company’s CRM platform, including attending to customer queries, troubleshooting issues, and handling technical requests</li>\n  <li>Assist in documenting support cases, escalating issues when necessary, and ensuring timely resolution to maintain customer satisfaction</li>\n  <li>Support in preparing technical documentation, FAQs, and knowledge base articles to improve internal efficiency and customer self-service</li>\n  <li>Contribute to platform integrations, including pixel implementation (e.g., via JavaScript/GTM), SDK setups, and API-based workflows</li>\n  <li>Participate in testing, data validation, and quality assurance of integrations, ensuring accurate event tracking and maintaining data integrity across systems</li>\n  <li>Assist in internal process improvements, proof-of-concepts, and tool evaluations to support customer-facing and internal initiatives</li>\n  <li>Perform other related functions as assigned by your manager, supporting both customer-facing and internal initiatives</li>\n  <li>Responsible for ad-hoc assignments, functions, and other related duties as specified by your manager</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>What we’re looking for</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Available for a full time internship (6 months, paid internship)</li>\n  <li>Preferably a fresh graduate or final year student pursuing a Bachelor or higher Degree in Information Technology in a recognized institution of higher learning, with good academic achievements</li>\n  <li>A fast and continuous learner, especially in this fast changing technology driven environment</li>\n  <li>Detail oriented and highly organized</li>\n  <li>Ability to prioritize, multi-task, and perform effectively under pressure</li>\n  <li>Have a strong interest in problem solving translated from data . </li>\n  <li>A good team player and aims to continue improving with the team and also able to work within and cross departments</li>\n  <li>Have basic knowledge on Microsoft office and Google Suite</li>\n  <li><strong>Proficiency in Mandarin, with the ability to communicate effectively in both writing and speaking</strong></li>\n  <li>Interest in and familiarity with AI tools (e.g., ChatGPT, Gemini) and a basic understanding of AI concepts such as LLMs, prompting, and AI agents. You’ll have opportunities to apply these skills in real projects and grow your expertise with us.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Be exposed to and grow your knowledge across the Digital Marketing ecosystem, including Performance Marketing, SEO, Content Marketing, CRM and more</li>\n  <li>Competitive pay with an attractive, long-term compensation model</li>\n  <li>A flat and open culture that nurtures entrepreneurism and wants to unlock the best version of you.</li>\n  <li>Work with a diverse team of smart people who are also fun after work.</li>\n  <li>Opportunity to interact with colleagues from different countries and cultures.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>"}
{"job_title": "Back End Engineer", "job_location": "Jakarta - Indonesia", "job_department": "Software Engineer", "job_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs/771728f3-2d9a-4024-96e3-336fcbb698a1", "first_seen": "2026-04-21 16:03:37", "base_salary": "0", "job_type": "Full-time", "job_level": "1 - 4 years", "job_apply_end_date": "2026-04-05 08:47:59", "last_seen": "2026-03-06 08:47:59", "is_active": "True", "company": "Makmur", "company_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/companies/makmurid", "job_board": "Tech in Asia Jobs", "job_board_url": "https://www.techinasia.com/jobs", "job_age": "expired", "work_arrangement": "On-site", "desc": "Back End Engineer Software Engineer <p>We're seeking an experienced Senior Backend Engineer to design and scale our server-side infrastructure. You'll work on developing robust APIs, optimizing database performance, and architecting distributed systems that power our platform. </p>\n<p>This is a high-impact role where you'll solve complex technical challenges and mentor other engineers while working with cutting-edge technologies.</p>\n<p><strong>Job Descriptions</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Design, develop, and maintain scalable backend services using Node.js and Express</li>\n  <li>Build and optimize REST and GraphQL APIs that serve millions of requests</li>\n  <li>Architect database solutions using MongoDB and implement caching strategies with Redis</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with frontend engineers to deliver end-to-end features</li>\n  <li>Implement comprehensive testing strategies (unit, integration, E2E)</li>\n  <li>Participate in on-call rotations and incident response</li>\n  <li>Mentor junior engineers and establish engineering best practices</li>\n  <li>Drive technical decisions and contribute to system architecture</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul><li>3+ years of professional software engineering experience</li>\n  <li>Solid understanding of algorithms and data structures for building efficient solutions</li>\n  <li>Strong ability to write modular, maintainable, and testable code following clean architecture principles and dependency injection</li>\n  <li>Strong proficiency in Node.js and Express, including middleware, routing, and async patterns</li>\n  <li>Extensive experience designing and implementing REST APIs and GraphQL services</li>\n  <li>Solid understanding of MongoDB, including schema design, indexing, and aggregations</li>\n  <li>Experience with Redis for caching and session management</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of authentication/authorization patterns (JWT, OAuth, session management)</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of microservices and event-driven architecture</li>\n  <li>Experience writing comprehensive tests and documentation that follow best practices and support long-term scalability</li>\n  <li>Proficient in version control systems (Git)</li>\n  <li>Eager to learn with a growth mindset and adaptability</li>\n  <li>Solid problem-solving and debugging capabilities</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Nice to Have</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Background in distributed systems and scalability patterns</li>\n  <li>Experience in building event-driven applications using message queues (Redis Stream)</li>\n  <li>Experience in building high-performance applications (C++)</li>\n  <li>Experience in building real-time systems using socket-based communication</li>\n  <li>Experience in applying best practices to design and handle high-frequency data streaming systems with a focus on performance and efficiency</li>\n  <li>Experience in automation and scheduling using scripting languages (Bash, Python)</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of containerization and orchestration (Docker, Kubernetes)</li>\n  <li>Experience in handling Protocol Buffer (Protobuf) messages for efficient data serialization.</li>\n  <li>Skilled in designing and implementing API gateways for third-party integrations (authentication, authorization, request routing, throttling, monitoring, error handling).</li>\n  <li>Proficient in cloud platforms and services, preferably AWS.</li>\n  <li>Previous experience leading technical projects or teams</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>"}
